<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1938-12-10T15:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1938-12-10T15:00:00-05:00" n="486" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d486">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">865.4016/120: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the Chargé in Italy</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Reed</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1938-12-10T15:00:00-05:00">December 10, 1938—3
                                        p.m.</date></dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>125. Your 367, December 9, 5 p.m. In reply to requests for advice you
                                should make it clear that the American Government does not admit the
                                right of a foreign government to discriminate between Americans on
                                account of race or creed; that it will maintain this position in any
                                protests it may make, but that each citizen must decide for himself
                                what action he may consider most useful in connection with his
                                individual case.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Welles</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>